"v.摇尾乞怜，奴颜婢膝 【英】 v. 摇尾乞怜，奴颜婢膝( to behave humbly or abjectly; stoop) 【考】 pluck : quit / pride : grovel(放弃不会有勇气/奴 颜婢膝不会有傲气) 【例】 He said he would never grovel before a conqueror. v. 摇尾乞怜; 卑躬屈膝; 自甘下贱; 阿谀奉承 = stoop = cringe 【记】建立场景: 两个角斗士(gladiator: 见到别人生病ia就高兴glad的人tor)在grove(grow five)小树林里决斗, 其中一方输了, 要卑躬屈膝, 单膝跪倒, 还要一手把剑l插在地上. Grove＋l = grovel－卑躬屈膝 【区】gravel(n 砂砾); groove(n 唱片等的凹槽) 【类】pluck: quit = pride: grovel放弃不会有勇气 = 奴颜婢膝不会有傲气imperious: grovel 傲慢的不会卑躬屈膝 【记】音：哥饶我，趴在地上叩头，大哥，饶了我吧，我服了你了 grovel (v.)  1590s, Shakespearian back-formation of groveling (Middle English), regarded as a present participle but really an adverb, from Old Norse grufe ""prone"" + obsolete adverbial suffix -ling (which survives also as the -long in headlong, sidelong); first element from Old Norse a grufu ""on proneness."" Perhaps related to creep. Related: Groveled; grovelled; groveling; grovelling."
